cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.DB, cs.SE

This paper presents a benchmark of stream processing throughput, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The comparison is made between Apache Spark Streaming and a prototype P2P stream processing framework, which involves network communication (cs.NI) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also explores the performance characteristics of these frameworks, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
